column5: Had my own marvellous morning, no dingbats at the boat launch, no wild wind.  Head east down K Bay, hit the 90 foot mark start marking like crazy, big fish under clouds of bait.  Hooked a nice 8lber, took about 10 minutes to land.  Back home, toys put away and fish cleaned by 10:15.
Awsome , hope there were less bugs then yesterday for you .
Bugs?... no bugs at all, bunch of dead ones floating that the little Herring were jumping for.
You sure they weren't carp?:whistling:LOL. Nice fish!!!!
They were herring.We seen them come right out of the water at times.  Nice fish bud.We got off at 2 pm.Extreamly awesome day.LOTS OF BUGS where we were.
